the half of it.

357
00:21:52,412 --> 00:21:54,614
This world is built
by the people on the inside.

358
00:21:54,647 --> 00:21:57,684
A little advantage can mean
the difference between

359
00:21:57,717 --> 00:22:00,920
Living a common,
unremarkable life

360
00:22:00,953 --> 00:22:03,423
And a life that can
change the world.

361
00:22:03,456 --> 00:22:05,625
I'm not trying to change
the world, Miss Cunningham.

362
00:22:05,658 --> 00:22:07,394
I'm just trying to
get back on the team

363
00:22:07,427 --> 00:22:09,095
And see my boyfriend.

364
00:22:09,128 --> 00:22:10,763
Yes, that's all
well and good,

365
00:22:10,797 --> 00:22:14,367
But there's a bigger picture
here, don't you see?

366
00:22:14,401 --> 00:22:17,704
It's about claiming
what is yours, Bridgette.

367
00:22:17,737 --> 00:22:19,706
You can't just wait for it
to come to you.

368
00:22:19,739 --> 00:22:21,574
You've got to
reach out and grab it,

369
00:22:21,608 --> 00:22:23,743
Grab what's rightfully yours,
yours by birth.

370
00:22:27,113 --> 00:22:31,951
With a little help,
you can have everything...

371
00:22:31,984 --> 00:22:34,587
And I'm that little help.

372
00:22:35,755 --> 00:22:37,457
Really?

373
00:22:39,792 --> 00:22:42,795
Don't imagine for a second
this doesn't happen everywhere,

374
00:22:42,829 --> 00:22:44,731
Including Edgington Academy.

375
00:22:44,764 --> 00:22:47,834
How do you think we have such
a flawless graduation record?

376
00:22:47,867 --> 00:22:50,169
You'd be amazed to know
the names of others

377
00:22:50,202 --> 00:22:52,104
Who have had help making it

378
00:22:52,138 --> 00:22:54,006
Through the rigors
of this environment.

379
00:22:54,040 --> 00:22:56,509
