00:49:24,529 --> 00:49:26,331
I don't need this anymore.

777
00:49:32,303 --> 00:49:33,638
I have to go.

778
00:49:34,172 --> 00:49:39,177
[***]

779
00:50:03,101 --> 00:50:05,103
[Knock on door]

780
00:50:05,136 --> 00:50:07,072
Jane.

781
00:50:08,606 --> 00:50:10,775
Uh, did your bulb go out?

782
00:50:10,808 --> 00:50:12,577
I could call maintenance.

783
00:50:12,610 --> 00:50:15,780
I was just about to
head over to the cafeteria

784
00:50:15,813 --> 00:50:19,317
To get some dinner,
if you'd like to join.

785
00:50:21,786 --> 00:50:24,689
I mean,
if you're not too busy.

786
00:50:24,722 --> 00:50:29,127
I just thought maybe
we should talk about our...

787
00:50:29,160 --> 00:50:31,028
Well, about us.

788
00:50:34,132 --> 00:50:38,436
I can't stop thinking
about the other night...

789
00:50:38,469 --> 00:50:41,306
Which was so wonderful.

790
00:50:43,208 --> 00:50:51,849
You asked me to express
certain feelings,

791
00:50:51,882 --> 00:50:55,286
And I was just wondering
if that was because

792
00:50:55,320 --> 00:50:57,155
You had similar feelings
towards me.

793
00:50:57,188 --> 00:50:58,456
Okay.

794
00:50:58,489 --> 00:51:01,058
Maybe we could
talk about this later.

795
00:51:03,361 --> 00:51:05,330
But I have to go.

796
00:51:06,697 --> 00:51:08,666
Uh, sure, sure.
Of course.

797
00:51:08,699 --> 00:51:14,172
[Laugh]
Sorry to have interrupted...

798
00:51:14,205 --> 00:51:15,840
Whatever you're doing...

799
00:51:18,443 --> 00:51:19,644
In the dark.

800
00:51:32,323 --> 00:51:34,625
[Bobby] So, my parents really
like you, if you can't tell.

801
00:51:34,659 --> 00:51:37,462
[Laugh]
I like them, too.

802
00:51:37,495 --> 00:51:40,131
Bridgette, what is it?

803
00:51:40,931 --> 00:51:44,435
[Sigh] What if, what if
I don't get into college?

804
00:51:44,469 --> 00:51:47,305
What if I can't make it
outside of Edgington?

805
00:51:47,338 --> 00:51:48,673
Says the girl
who just kicked ass

806
00:51:48,706 --> 00:51:50,908
In all of her midterms?

807
00:51:50,941 --> 00:51:52,677
I don't deserve to be here.

808
00:51:52,710 --> 00:51:57,282
I was just born
into the right family.

809
00:51:57,315 --> 00:51:59,584
Well, Miss Cunningham
seems to think

810
00:51:59,617 --> 00:52:01,486
That you're pretty special.

811
00:52:03,954 --> 00:52:05,423
Right?

812
00:52:05,456 --> 00:52:07,525
What's going on
between you two?

813
00:52:09,594 --> 00:52:13,331
Whatever it is,
you can tell me.

814
00:52:15,900 --> 00:52:17,835
Bridgette?

815
00:52:21,839 --> 00:52:23,374
[Phone vibrates]

816
00:52:29,447 --> 00:52:30,681
Miss Cunningham?

817
00:52:30,715 --> 00:52:32,617
[Jane]
Bridgette, come in!

818
00:52:34,252 --> 00:52:36,454
You said
there was an emergency?

819
00:52:36,487 --> 00:52:38,923
Right. College admissions
deadlines are fast approaching,

820
00:52:38,956 --> 00:52:41,226
And we need to work on
your personal statement.

821
00:52:41,259 --> 00:52:43,228
- Miss Cunningham...
- Jane.

822
00:52:43,261 --> 00:52:44,795
Miss Cunningham,
I really appreciate

823
00:52:44,829 --> 00:52:46,531
Everything you've done for me,

824
00:52:46,564 --> 00:52:49,300
But I should really just do
my own college applications.

825
00:52:49,334 --> 00:52:51,769
That's a very mature thing
to say.

826
00:52:54,705 --> 00:52:58,376
I think I should start taking
responsibility for myself.

827
00:52:58,409 --> 00:52:59,710
Right.

828
00:53:02,247 --> 00:53:04,482
So, tattoos?

829
00:53:06,651 --> 00:53:08,986
[Bridgette] Thanks for getting
them all. I'll read them over

830
00:53:09,019 --> 00:53:11,256
And let you know
if I have any questions.

831
00:53:12,490 --> 00:53:14,292
Please have a cookie.

832
00:53:15,960 --> 00:53:18,929
I'd love to, but I...
I have practice in the morning,

833
00:53:18,963 --> 00:53:20,865
And I should just get to sleep.

834
00:53:20,898 --> 00:53:23,000
I spent all night
decorating these.

835
00:53:23,033 --> 00:53:25,803
At least take a few back to
the room for you and Danielle.

836
00:53:33,844 --> 00:53:35,280
What is that?

837
00:53:42,787 --> 00:53:44,322
You went without me?

838
00:53:47,057 --> 00:53:49,260
We were supposed to
get those together.

839
00:53:50,027 --> 00:53:53,798
It wasn't about you.
It was about my team.

840
00:53:53,831 --> 00:53:55,800
My friends.

841
00:53:57,602 --> 00:54:00,838
[Plate crashing]
[yelling] I am your friend!

842
00:54:00,871 --> 00:54:02,673
When you got
kicked off the team,

843
00:54:02,707 --> 00:54:04,675
They all just went on
with their lives.

844
00:54:04,709 --> 00:54:07,545
I dropped everything for you!

845
00:54:11,015 --> 00:54:13,451
You can't just
walk away from me!

846
00:54:15,586 --> 00:54:18,556
My mother
was right about you.

847
00:54:19,824 --> 00:54:21,258
Bridgette.

848
00:54:21,892 --> 00:54:23,294
[Door closes]

849
00:54:23,328 --> 00:54:24,562
Bridgette!

850
00:54:25,896 --> 00:54:27,498
[Yelling]
Bridgette!

851
00:54:29,367 --> 00:54:31,869
[Yelling] Bridgette,
come back here!

852
00:54:31,902 --> 00:54:33,604
Bridgette!

853
00:54:33,638 --> 00:54:34,905
Bridgette!

854
00:54:34,939 --> 00:54:36,707
[Yelling]
Bridgette!

855
00:55:00,865 --> 00:55:02,299
Jane!

856
00:55:06,971 --> 00:55:10,441
Um, uh, I was afraid I'd done
something to upset you.

857
00:55:10,475 --> 00:55:12,843
Why would you think that?

858
00:55:12,877 --> 00:55:14,345
I don't know.

859
00:55:15,780 --> 00:55:19,350
You know that thing
you wanted to talk about?

860
00:55:19,384 --> 00:55:20,585
That thing?

861
00:55:20,618 --> 00:55:23,087
I told you
we could talk about it later?

862
00:55:23,120 --> 00:55:24,622
Okay, I'm ready.

863
00:55:24,655 --> 00:55:26,056
We can talk about it
right now.

864
00:55:27,057 --> 00:55:30,528
Oh, uh, um, well that's...

865
00:55:31,596 --> 00:55:32,830
Well that's...

866
00:55:34,131 --> 00:55:36,567
Sort of a private matter,
don't you think?

867
00:55:36,601 --> 00:55:37,768
No.

868
00:55:37,802 --> 00:55:40,037
Okay. Okay.

869
00:55:41,772 --> 00:55:47,412
Um, listen, Jane,

870
00:55:47,445 --> 00:55:49,146
Don't you think
it would be better

871
00:55:49,179 --> 00:55:51,148
If we did this privately?

872
00:55:51,181 --> 00:55:53,918
I mean, maybe
we could have dinner.

873
00:55:53,951 --> 00:55:56,654
- Dinner?
- Yeah.

874
00:55:56,687 --> 00:55:59,724
Why would I have dinner
with you?

875
00:55:59,757 --> 00:56:02,059
Uh, what?

876
00:56:02,092 --> 00:56:04,161
Do you really think
someone like me

877
00:56:04,194 --> 00:56:06,631
Would go out
with someone like you?

878
00:56:09,133 --> 00:56:11,702
You can't dress yourself.
Your breath smells.

879
00:56:11,736 --> 00:56:14,739
Your beard is disgusting,
and your hair is falling out.

880
00:56:14,772 --> 00:56:19,477
Your penis is minuscule.
No one likes you.

881
00:56:19,510 --> 00:56:22,580
You're only good at one subject,
the most boring subject,

882
00:56:22,613 --> 00:56:24,915
And right now you've got
soup on your face,

883
00:56:24,949 --> 00:56:27,384
And you don't even know it!

884
00:56:30,855 --> 00:56:32,557
Well, doesn't he?

885
00:56:41,165 --> 00:56:43,133
[***]

886
00:56:43,167 --> 00:56:46,170
[Door opens]

887
00:56:53,944 --> 00:56:55,846
What's going on?

888
00:56:55,880 --> 00:56:58,649
They're putting me
in Pinehurst House.

889
00:57:00,518 --> 00:57:01,852
But that's the dorm for...

890
00:57:01,886 --> 00:57:03,888
Kids who try to
hurt themselves?

891
00:57:03,921 --> 00:57:07,191
Yeah, it is.

892
00:57:07,224 --> 00:57:08,859
I don't understand.

893
00:57:08,893 --> 00:57:10,895
[Sighs] Well, apparently
there was a report

894
00:57:10,928 --> 00:57:13,798
That my eating disorder
is back.

895
00:57:13,831 --> 00:57:15,633
[Sighs]

896
00:57:15,666 --> 00:57:16,867
Is it?

897
00:57:18,669 --> 00:57:19,870
No!

898
00:57:23,007 --> 00:57:24,575
Who would say that?

899
00:57:26,210 --> 00:57:27,512
Who do you think?

900
00:57:31,582 --> 00:57:33,050
We... we've got to do
something.

901
00:57:33,083 --> 00:57:36,220
- We've got to tell somebody.
- Tell somebody?

902
00:57:36,253 --> 00:57:38,489
You don't think
I've already tried?

903
00:57:38,523 --> 00:57:40,525
You think they're
going to believe me?

904
00:57:40,558 --> 00:57:42,126
My shuttle is waiting.

905
00:57:42,159 --> 00:57:46,096
If you want to find me,
look for the short bus.

906
00:57:46,130 --> 00:57:49,066
[Door opens and closes]

907
00:57:56,941 --> 00:57:58,976
[Cell phone notification]

908
00:58:18,996 --> 00:58:20,731
Bridgette.

909
00:58:25,035 --> 00:58:26,571
Bridge?

910
00:58:30,608 --> 00:58:31,942
Where are you?

911
00:58:36,847 --> 00:58:38,749
Hah, you found them.

912
00:58:47,057 --> 00:58:48,593
Bridgette.

913
00:59:16,186 --> 00:59:17,722
Oh, man.

914
00:59:18,923 --> 00:59:21,592
Bridgette, what are you doing?

915
00:59:26,897 --> 00:59:28,565
You are crazy!

916
00:59:30,000 --> 00:59:31,769
Jesus, Bridgette.

917
00:59:34,639 --> 00:59:38,075
[Groans]

918
00:59:51,121 --> 00:59:52,657
[Groans]
[scream]

919
00:59:52,690 --> 00:59:54,224
Hey, come back!

920
00:59:54,258 --> 00:59:55,760
Get away from me!

921
00:59:55,793 --> 00:59:57,261
Get away from me!
[sobs]

922
00:59:57,294 --> 00:59:58,863
Get on the ground, now!

923
00:59:58,896 --> 01:00:01,131
- [Sobs]
- Hands behind your back.

924
01:00:01,165 --> 01:00:03,901
[Sobs]

925
01:00:11,008 --> 01:00:12,810
Miss Cunningham?

926
01:00:15,045 --> 01:00:18,082
[Sobs]

927
01:00:18,115 --> 01:00:20,951
Thank God you came!

928
01:00:20,985 --> 01:00:25,122
He lured me
under the bleachers.

929
01:00:25,155 --> 01:00:28,325
[Sobs]

930
01:00:30,728 --> 01:00:31,929
[Phone dings]

931
01:00:33,297 --> 01:00:35,132
Hello.

932
01:00:35,165 --> 01:00:37,301
Bobby! Bobby, are you okay?

933
01:00:37,334 --> 01:00:39,069
I've been arrested.

934
01:00:40,838 --> 01:00:44,041
Miss Cunningham.
It was a setup.

935
01:00:44,074 --> 01:00:45,810
She had them put me in jail.

936
01:00:45,843 --> 01:00:48,345
No matter what they tell you,
she made it look like...

937
01:00:48,378 --> 01:00:50,915
Like I...

938
01:00:50,948 --> 01:00:52,216
Okay, I gotta go.

939
01:00:52,249 --> 01:00:53,450
I'm so sorry, Bridgette.

940
01:00:53,483 --> 01:00:55,686
I thought it was you. I swear.

941
01:00:57,454 --> 01:00:58,956
Bobby!

942
01:01:02,226 --> 01:01:03,728
Bridgette, come in.

943
01:01:03,761 --> 01:01:05,295
I just opened
a bottle of wine.

944
01:01:05,329 --> 01:01:07,131
Why are you doing this?

945
01:01:07,164 --> 01:01:08,465
Doing what?

946
01:01:08,498 --> 01:01:10,801
I know what you did
to Bobby and Danni.

947
01:01:10,835 --> 01:01:12,737
Look, whatever happened
to your friends,

948
01:01:12,770 --> 01:01:14,371
I'm sure they got
what they deserved.

949
01:01:14,404 --> 01:01:15,773
They weren't good for you.

950
01:01:15,806 --> 01:01:17,241
You're not good for me!

951
01:01:17,274 --> 01:01:19,710
I'd bite your tongue,
if I were you.

952
01:01:19,744 --> 01:01:22,112
You saw how easy it was
for your grades to get better.

953
01:01:22,146 --> 01:01:23,748
How hard do you think
it would be

954
01:01:23,781 --> 01:01:25,082
For them to get worse again?

955
01:01:25,115 --> 01:01:26,416
Miss Cunningham...

956
01:01:26,450 --> 01:01:29,453
Jane. You know
you can call me Jane.

957
01:01:31,155 --> 01:01:33,323
[Door opens and closes]

958
01:01:33,357 --> 01:01:34,825
[Bridgette]
Mom?

959
01:01:37,261 --> 01:01:39,429
Are you okay?

960
01:01:39,463 --> 01:01:42,933
I just got off the phone
with the headmaster.

961
01:01:42,967 --> 01:01:45,469
He told me about Bobby.

962
01:01:45,502 --> 01:01:47,171
Yeah.

963
01:01:47,204 --> 01:01:51,241
His dad's on the way down
to post bail.

964
01:01:51,275 --> 01:01:53,010
That woman is insane.

965
01:01:53,043 --> 01:01:55,512
The board and York
believe Bobby is innocent,

966
01:01:55,545 --> 01:01:57,214
And we think
the police will, too.

967
01:01:57,247 --> 01:02:00,117
Of course he's innocent.
She should be the one in jail.

968
01:02:02,486 --> 01:02:05,089
She almost was...

969
01:02:05,122 --> 01:02:06,323
Once.

970
01:02:09,827 --> 01:02:13,898
Her three-year sabbatical
was not voluntary.

971
01:02:13,931 --> 01:02:18,335
It was prompted by an alleged
obsession with a student.

972
01:02:21,505 --> 01:02:23,340
So she's done this before.

973
01:02:27,177 --> 01:02:28,913
How could you
let her come back?

974
01:02:28,946 --> 01:02:30,915
Why didn't you turn her in?

975
01:02:30,948 --> 01:02:32,416
We had no solid proof,

976
01:02:32,449 --> 01:02:35,786
Certainly nothing
that would stand up in court.

977
01:02:35,820 --> 01:02:38,355
We decided our best option
was to send Jane

978
01:02:38,388 --> 01:02:45,429
As far away as possible
until it all blew over,

979
01:02:45,462 --> 01:02:48,799
And poor Hannah could get
the help she needed.

980
01:02:48,833 --> 01:02:51,035
When you decided,
who was "we"?

981
01:02:56,306 --> 01:03:00,577
The board, Headmaster York.

982
01:03:00,610 --> 01:03:04,048
Something like this
can ruin a school, Bridgette,

983
01:03:04,081 --> 01:03:06,016
Even an allegation.

984
01:03:06,050 --> 01:03:07,885
But she's insane.
You have to do something!

985
01:03:07,918 --> 01:03:09,553
We're going to meet on it
tomorrow morning.

986
01:03:09,586 --> 01:03:11,155
She's dangerous, Mom.

987
01:03:11,188 --> 01:03:12,923
We don't have
a choice, Bridgette.

988
01:03:12,957 --> 01:03:14,291
Do you have any idea
how hard it is

989
01:03:14,324 --> 01:03:16,260
To fire a tenured teacher,

990
01:03:16,293 --> 01:03:18,162
And I can't afford
a scandal now.

991
01:03:18,195 --> 01:03:20,064
You don't get it, Mom.

992
01:03:22,499 --> 01:03:26,203
It's not just Danni
and Bobby she's after.

993
01:03:30,507 --> 01:03:33,210
Jane's been helping me.

994
01:03:34,411 --> 01:03:36,180
She changed my grades.

995
01:03:36,213 --> 01:03:38,115
She wrote the lit essay
for me...

996
01:03:39,483 --> 01:03:42,519
And she gave me the answers
to the calculus midterm.

997
01:03:46,656 --> 01:03:50,460
I'm sorry.
I know it was wrong,

998
01:03:50,494 --> 01:03:53,063
But, but I have the essay notes
in her handwriting,

999
01:03:53,097 --> 01:03:56,266
And we can use it as proof
that she cheated.

1000
01:03:56,300 --> 01:03:58,602
Hopefully it's enough
to get her fired,

1001
01:03:58,635 --> 01:04:01,171
Maybe even sent away.

1002
01:04:05,109 --> 01:04:06,944
[Sobs]
I'm really sorry.

1003
01:04:06,977 --> 01:04:08,478
I know it was wrong.

1004
01:04:08,512 --> 01:04:10,080
I didn't mean
for it to happen.

1005
01:04:10,114 --> 01:04:12,482
It just did.

1006
01:04:14,284 --> 01:04:17,421
Please say something.
Don't just sit there.

1007
01:04:20,124 --> 01:04:21,892
The same thing
happened to me.

1008
01:04:28,032 --> 01:04:31,368
Here, at Edgington,
25 years ago.

1009
01:04:31,401 --> 01:04:33,203
Oh my God!

1010
01:04:36,006 --> 01:04:38,909
Jane always had
a brilliant mind.

1011
01:04:38,943 --> 01:04:42,446
Socially inept,
mildly delusional...

1012
01:04:45,315 --> 01:04:47,651
But completely brilliant.

1013
01:04:47,684 --> 01:04:50,254
It... it started out
as nothing.

1014
01:04:51,621 --> 01:04:54,925
I would come in late
from play rehearsal exhausted,

1015
01:04:54,959 --> 01:04:57,327
And she'd talk me
through the homework.

1016
01:04:59,229 --> 01:05:02,332
But it kept progressing.

1017
01:05:02,366 --> 01:05:04,568
I had no time to study.

1018
01:05:04,601 --> 01:05:06,170
I was class president.

1019
01:05:06,203 --> 01:05:08,238
I was captain
of the volleyball team.

1020
01:05:08,272 --> 01:05:12,576
I was lead in the fall play,
and the more I took on,

1021
01:05:12,609 --> 01:05:14,511
The more I needed her.

1022
01:05:15,545 --> 01:05:17,447
And I let her do it for me.

1023
01:05:21,418 --> 01:05:24,221
And before I knew it,
it just...

1024
01:05:25,222 --> 01:05:26,923
I know.

1025
01:05:28,058 --> 01:05:29,626
Jane...

1026
01:05:31,428 --> 01:05:33,597
She did my application.

1027
01:05:33,630 --> 01:05:35,299
She got me in.

1028
01:05:37,367 --> 01:05:39,203
But look what it got me.

1029
01:05:39,236 --> 01:05:40,670
This.

1030
01:05:41,505 --> 01:05:43,273
A career.

1031
01:05:43,307 --> 01:05:47,111
A standing in the community.

1032
01:05:47,144 --> 01:05:49,146
Respect.

1033
01:05:49,179 --> 01:05:51,148
Everything I always wanted.

1034
01:05:56,486 --> 01:05:58,422
You're not going to do
anything.

1035
01:06:00,624 --> 01:06:02,126
Are you?

1036
01:06:05,362 --> 01:06:07,364
You're afraid
she'll expose you.

1037
01:06:31,221 --> 01:06:32,622
Cornell?

1038
01:06:34,491 --> 01:06:35,692
Jane?

1039
01:06:38,262 --> 01:06:39,629
Yeah.

1040
01:06:42,332 --> 01:06:46,203
[Laugh]

1041
01:06:46,236 --> 01:06:48,072
You've gotta go.

1042
01:06:48,105 --> 01:06:49,306
What? Are you serious?

1043
01:06:49,339 --> 01:06:51,608
If you don't play
by her rules,

1044
01:06:51,641 --> 01:06:54,444
She will out you
as a cheater.

1045
01:06:54,478 --> 01:06:57,281
You'll be kicked
out of Edgington.

1046
01:06:57,314 --> 01:06:59,683
You'll be a pariah
at any Ivy League school.

1047
01:07:02,752 --> 01:07:05,289
This is your future,
Bridgette,

1048
01:07:05,322 --> 01:07:07,557
The rest of your life
we're talking about.

1049
01:07:11,095 --> 01:07:13,530
What, so I'm just
supposed to play along?

1050
01:07:17,567 --> 01:07:19,736
Yes.

1051
01:07:19,769 --> 01:07:23,607
And then you can go off
to Cornell and start over

1052
01:07:23,640 --> 01:07:25,809
And forget
any of this ever happened.

1053
01:07:30,380 --> 01:07:32,382
Have you forgotten it, Mom?

1054
01:07:37,354 --> 01:07:43,360
[***]

1055
01:07:43,393 --> 01:07:47,731
* How did you take me
this far *

1056
01:07:47,764 --> 01:07:52,336
* My, oh my

1057
01:07:52,369 --> 01:07:56,673
* I wasn't prepared
from the start *

1058
01:07:56,706 --> 01:08:01,445
* For life, oh I

1059
01:08:01,478 --> 01:08:05,382
* I should tell the truth

1060
01:08:05,415 --> 01:08:09,886
* But I lie to you

1061
01:08:09,919 --> 01:08:14,391
* But if you to

1062
01:08:14,424 --> 01:08:18,728
* I will die for you

1063
01:08:18,762 --> 01:08:26,403
* Because I lose

1064
01:08:26,436 --> 01:08:33,210
* Time after time,
so I use... *

1065
01:09:31,768 --> 01:09:33,737
I'm sorry.

1066
01:09:33,770 --> 01:09:35,872
I... I just had to see you.

1067
01:09:37,507 --> 01:09:39,476
I let myself in.
I fell asleep waiting for you.

1068
01:09:39,509 --> 01:09:41,878
I... I hope you don't mind.

1069
01:09:41,911 --> 01:09:44,581
Of course not.

1070
01:09:44,614 --> 01:09:47,451
Are you all right?

1071
01:09:47,484 --> 01:09:49,319
I don't like being alone.

1072
01:09:57,461 --> 01:09:59,929
I'm... I'm so sorry.

1073
01:09:59,963 --> 01:10:03,467
I'm so sorry
for what Bobby did to you.

1074
01:10:03,500 --> 01:10:04,734
I should have
seen it coming.

1075
01:10:04,768 --> 01:10:06,870
He was always
talking about you.

1076
01:10:06,903 --> 01:10:09,005
I just can't believe
he did what he did.

1077
01:10:09,038 --> 01:10:10,407
I'll be fine.

1078
01:10:10,440 --> 01:10:11,675
Don't you worry about me.

1079
01:10:11,708 --> 01:10:13,643
And Danni.

1080
01:10:13,677 --> 01:10:17,581
She was just
so jealous of me...

1081
01:10:17,614 --> 01:10:19,883
Of you and me.

1082
01:10:19,916 --> 01:10:22,586
At times, we don't want
to see the signs of illness

1083
01:10:22,619 --> 01:10:24,521
In the people we love.

1084
01:10:26,323 --> 01:10:28,858
I realize now just what
you were trying to do for me.

1085
01:10:30,026 --> 01:10:32,996
I understand now the way
things work in the real world.

1086
01:10:35,299 --> 01:10:38,702
I didn't get that before,
but I get that now.

1087
01:10:38,735 --> 01:10:40,537
- I'm just here to help.
- I know.

1088
01:10:42,406 --> 01:10:44,474
Just like you helped
my mother.

1089
01:10:44,508 --> 01:10:45,775
She told you?

1090
01:10:48,077 --> 01:10:50,847
I saw something
in your mother.

1091
01:10:50,880 --> 01:10:53,383
I knew it
from the moment we met.

1092
01:10:53,417 --> 01:10:55,419
She had something.

1093
01:10:55,452 --> 01:10:57,687
Everyone was drawn to her.

1094
01:10:57,721 --> 01:10:59,523
She had the light.

1095
01:11:01,658 --> 01:11:03,360
And you were
such good friends.

1096
01:11:03,393 --> 01:11:05,795
We were.
We were, indeed.

1097
01:11:05,829 --> 01:11:07,397
And you did so much

1098
01:11:07,431 --> 01:11:09,866
To help her to get her
where she is today.

1099
01:11:12,869 --> 01:11:14,904
I'm sorry you drifted apart.

1100
01:11:14,938 --> 01:11:18,775
It was inevitable,
but I'm happy for your mother,

1101
01:11:18,808 --> 01:11:21,711
And I'm happy I could
help her in some small way.

1102
01:11:24,113 --> 01:11:27,517
You have the gift, Bridgette.

1103
01:11:27,551 --> 01:11:29,486
I saw it in you

1104
01:11:29,519 --> 01:11:32,889
The very same way
as I saw it in your mother.

1105
01:11:32,922 --> 01:11:35,925
Everyone is born
with a purpose.

1106
01:11:35,959 --> 01:11:40,697
I recognized at a very early age
that I don't have that light,

1107
01:11:40,730 --> 01:11:43,533
That spark that you
and your mother have.

1108
01:11:43,567 --> 01:11:45,435
But what I do have

1109
01:11:45,469 --> 01:11:48,605
Is the ability to recognize
those lights in others

1110
01:11:48,638 --> 01:11:51,941
And help those light bearers
achieve their destinies.

1111
01:11:53,543 --> 01:11:57,013
You really think I'm a light
bearer, Miss Cunningham?

1112
01:11:57,046 --> 01:11:59,015
Jane.

1113
01:11:59,048 --> 01:12:02,652
Oh, I know so.
It's my gift, remember?

1114
01:12:04,621 --> 01:12:06,656
Your light is bright, my dear.

1115
01:12:06,690 --> 01:12:08,392
I have so much to learn.

1116
01:12:09,759 --> 01:12:11,361
Teach me.

1117
01:12:12,962 --> 01:12:14,664
Help me.

1118
01:12:24,408 --> 01:12:34,350
[***]

1119
01:12:43,460 --> 01:12:45,629
Okay. Just make this
a little bit more clear.

1120
01:12:45,662 --> 01:12:46,930
Okay.

1121
01:12:48,197 --> 01:12:50,767
[Phone vibrates]

1122
01:12:50,800 --> 01:12:54,070
Sorry. I don't recognize
this number. I better get it.

1123
01:12:54,103 --> 01:12:55,872
Hello?

1124
01:12:55,905 --> 01:12:57,106
Yes, it is.

1125
01:13:01,177 --> 01:13:03,913
Are you serious?

1126
01:13:03,947 --> 01:13:06,082
Oh my God!
Yes, th... thank you.

1127
01:13:06,115 --> 01:13:08,051
Thank you so much!

1128
01:13:09,152 --> 01:13:11,655
I'm a finalist for Eurotour!

1129
01:13:11,688 --> 01:13:15,592
Bridgette, that's amazing!
Congratulations!

1130
01:13:15,625 --> 01:13:17,861
Tryouts are this weekend,
upstate.

1131
01:13:17,894 --> 01:13:21,698
Oh, it's so exciting!

1132
01:13:21,731 --> 01:13:23,933
I have a great idea.

1133
01:13:23,967 --> 01:13:26,002
How about you come up
with me?

1134
01:13:26,035 --> 01:13:27,604
- To the trials?
- Yes.

1135
01:13:27,637 --> 01:13:29,639
We'll have so much fun
on the trip,

1136
01:13:29,673 --> 01:13:31,908
And maybe on the way back,
we can stop in New York City,

1137
01:13:31,941 --> 01:13:34,444
Catch a show,
see a couple of museums.

1138
01:13:36,513 --> 01:13:38,748
I don't know.
Just the two of us?

1139
01:13:38,782 --> 01:13:41,751
Yeah! A weekender.
We'll have a blast!

1140
01:13:43,687 --> 01:13:45,088
Okay!

1141
01:13:45,789 --> 01:13:49,092
[Cheers]

1142
01:14:17,754 --> 01:14:18,955
All set?

1143
01:14:20,056 --> 01:14:21,725
Where's your stuff?

1144
01:14:24,661 --> 01:14:25,995
Bridgette, is something wrong?

1145
01:14:27,731 --> 01:14:29,899
You're one crazy bitch!

1146
01:14:31,568 --> 01:14:33,570
I beg your pardon?

1147
01:14:34,804 --> 01:14:36,139
Come on. Let's go!

1148
01:14:36,172 --> 01:14:39,075
You're not going anywhere.

1149
01:14:39,108 --> 01:14:40,644
But what about Eurotour?

1150
01:14:40,677 --> 01:14:42,011
Jane, stop!

1151
01:14:44,047 --> 01:14:46,182
I've had enough of you.

1152
01:14:46,215 --> 01:14:48,051
My mother
has had enough of you.

1153
01:14:48,084 --> 01:14:51,988
All those girls you've ruined
have had enough of you!

1154
01:14:53,289 --> 01:14:55,291
You're evil,

1155
01:14:55,324 --> 01:15:00,163
And you're going away
for a long, long time.

1156
01:15:01,130 --> 01:15:02,799
Bridgette...

1157
01:15:03,867 --> 01:15:05,835
Don't do this.

1158
01:15:05,869 --> 01:15:08,738
- You need me.
- I don't need you!

1159
01:15:08,772 --> 01:15:10,740
All that stuff about
you recognizing light

1160
01:15:10,774 --> 01:15:13,610
And helping others
is just your sick way

1161
01:15:13,643 --> 01:15:17,213
Of justifying your lonely
and obsessive existence.

1162
01:15:18,915 --> 01:15:21,117
I don't need you.

1163
01:15:21,150 --> 01:15:22,852
I have never needed you.

1164
01:15:22,886 --> 01:15:25,221
No one has ever needed you.

1165
01:15:25,254 --> 01:15:27,023
[Jane]
Bridgette!

1166
01:15:27,056 --> 01:15:30,259
Listen to what you're saying.

1167
01:15:30,293 --> 01:15:33,897
You could have everything,
and you're throwing it all away.

1168
01:15:33,930 --> 01:15:35,699
I want you to admit yourself

1169
01:15:35,732 --> 01:15:38,334
To St. Abigail's
psychiatric ward.

1170
01:15:38,367 --> 01:15:40,804
It's a lockdown
treatment facility.

1171
01:15:46,910 --> 01:15:49,813
I... will expose you...

1172
01:15:49,846 --> 01:15:51,981
For the cheat that you are.

1173
01:15:52,015 --> 01:15:54,751
You will never
graduate from here,

1174
01:15:54,784 --> 01:15:56,653
Much less go to Cornell

1175
01:15:56,686 --> 01:15:58,988
Or any other reputable
university for that matter.

1176
01:15:59,022 --> 01:16:02,291
Fine! So be it!

1177
01:16:02,325 --> 01:16:05,261
Headmaster York
is right outside these doors.

1178
01:16:05,294 --> 01:16:07,931
Now you come to your senses,
or I go straight out there

1179
01:16:07,964 --> 01:16:09,599
And I tell him
all about your cheating

1180
01:16:09,633 --> 01:16:10,934
And your mother's as well.

1181
01:16:10,967 --> 01:16:13,837
Jane,
I'm giving you a chance.

1182
01:16:13,870 --> 01:16:17,707
I won't go to the FBI
if you'll just comply.

1183
01:16:19,676 --> 01:16:21,344
FBI?

1184
01:16:21,377 --> 01:16:23,212
I'm afraid
giving prescription drugs

1185
01:16:23,246 --> 01:16:26,850
To a minor is a felony.

1186
01:16:26,883 --> 01:16:29,886
Oh, and those tapes
of Bobby and I having sex?

1187
01:16:31,254 --> 01:16:35,224
Hmm, I think the FBI frowns
upon child pornography.

1188
01:16:35,258 --> 01:16:38,027
[Fighting sounds]

1189
01:16:39,428 --> 01:16:42,999
[Screams]

1190
01:16:46,836 --> 01:16:49,873
[Cheers]

1191
01:17:00,750 --> 01:17:02,018
Say it!

1192
01:17:02,886 --> 01:17:04,053
Say you'll go!

1193
01:17:04,087 --> 01:17:06,022
Say you'll go,
or I'm going to the FBI.

1194
01:17:06,055 --> 01:17:07,757
- Okay. Let me up!
- You'll go?

1195
01:17:07,791 --> 01:17:11,227
- Yes.
- You'll go immediately.

1196
01:17:11,260 --> 01:17:12,896
Yes.

1197
01:17:12,929 --> 01:17:15,031
[Heavy breathing]

1198
01:17:30,179 --> 01:17:33,116
[Screams]

1199
01:17:38,054 --> 01:17:39,355
I dare you.

1200
01:17:41,224 --> 01:17:43,192
You think
you could blackmail me?

1201
01:17:43,226 --> 01:17:44,728
Huh?

1202
01:17:50,099 --> 01:17:51,768
[Scream]

1203
01:17:55,071 --> 01:17:58,174
[Heavy breathing]

1204
01:18:01,510 --> 01:18:02,912
Are you all right?

1205
01:18:02,946 --> 01:18:05,849
Oh, my baby! My baby!

1206
01:18:18,795 --> 01:18:20,196
Miss Berwitt,
are you all right?

1207
01:18:22,031 --> 01:18:24,367
Why would you do
all that alone?

1208
01:18:24,400 --> 01:18:26,069
That was reckless.

1209
01:18:26,102 --> 01:18:28,171
Indeed!
You could have been killed.

1210
01:18:28,204 --> 01:18:30,339
That woman is very dangerous.

1211
01:18:30,373 --> 01:18:32,041
Now you say so.

1212
01:18:32,075 --> 01:18:34,310
You should have never let
Jane Cunningham come back,

1213
01:18:34,343 --> 01:18:36,345
And you know it.

1214
01:18:36,379 --> 01:18:40,716
Yes, well, it's over now,
thanks to you.

1215
01:18:41,885 --> 01:18:43,386
Hold on, Headmaster.

1216
01:18:46,856 --> 01:18:48,491
I know what you did.

1217
01:18:48,524 --> 01:18:50,126
I know you played a part

1218
01:18:50,159 --> 01:18:53,262
In Jane Cunningham
coming back to Edgington,

1219
01:18:53,296 --> 01:18:57,233
And I know you were in cahoots
with Candace on the cover-up.

1220
01:18:59,002 --> 01:19:03,873
But we're going to put
all of that behind us right now.

1221
01:19:03,907 --> 01:19:05,942
Here's how it's gonna go.

1222
01:19:05,975 --> 01:19:07,944
Mom, effective immediately,

1223
01:19:07,977 --> 01:19:09,813
You're going to
turn in your resignation

1224
01:19:09,846 --> 01:19:12,115
As chairman
of the Edgington board.

1225
01:19:12,148 --> 01:19:13,783
Agreed?

1226
01:19:15,484 --> 01:19:16,986
Agreed.

1227
01:19:17,020 --> 01:19:18,922
[Bridgette]
And Headmaster York,

1228
01:19:18,955 --> 01:19:21,390
You are going to make
Edgington history

1229
01:19:21,424 --> 01:19:24,060
And grant me
a second chance...

1230
01:19:24,093 --> 01:19:28,031
A repeat of my senior year,
as well as reinstate

1231
01:19:28,064 --> 01:19:30,399
My position
as the lacrosse captain,

1232
01:19:30,433 --> 01:19:34,003
Once the very able
current captain

1233
01:19:34,037 --> 01:19:36,039
Completes the season.

1234
01:19:36,072 --> 01:19:41,010
In exchange, I will maintain
a 3.5 or above GPA

1235
01:19:41,044 --> 01:19:45,548
Throughout the year,
fairly and squarely.

1236
01:19:45,581 --> 01:19:47,350
No cheating.

1237
01:19:48,885 --> 01:19:50,086
Agreed?

1238
01:19:55,158 --> 01:19:56,559
Agreed.

1239
01:19:59,996 --> 01:20:02,098
[Swan honk]

1240
01:20:08,537 --> 01:20:10,506
[Candace] You're so brave.

1241
01:20:10,539 --> 01:20:12,876
If I had half your courage
when I was your age.

1242
01:20:12,909 --> 01:20:16,980
Hey, no more looking back,
Mom, only moving forward.

1243
01:20:18,547 --> 01:20:21,250
You did the right thing...

1244
01:20:21,284 --> 01:20:23,086
Giving up your position
on the board

1245
01:20:23,119 --> 01:20:25,821
And coming clean
with cheating in school.

1246
01:20:27,056 --> 01:20:30,126
I'm really proud of you,

1247
01:20:30,159 --> 01:20:34,030
And I'm really sorry it had
such an impact on your campaign.

1248
01:20:34,063 --> 01:20:35,531
I think you would have been

1249
01:20:35,564 --> 01:20:38,167
The best city councilman
probably ever.

1250
01:20:38,201 --> 01:20:40,503
[Laugh]

1251
01:20:44,140 --> 01:20:46,009
But I'm not sorry
it happened.

1252
01:20:48,077 --> 01:20:49,612
Things are better now.

1253
01:20:49,645 --> 01:20:52,248
Such a weight lifted.

1254
01:20:52,281 --> 01:20:54,383
I don't know
what I was so afraid of.

1255
01:20:54,417 --> 01:20:59,122
I haven't been this relaxed
in 25 years.

1256
01:20:59,155 --> 01:21:02,291
Well, a Berwitt
is never down for long.

1257
01:21:02,325 --> 01:21:04,627
What's next,
another campaign?

1258
01:21:04,660 --> 01:21:06,429
Another board?

1259
01:21:06,462 --> 01:21:08,364
President?
[laugh]

1260
01:21:08,397 --> 01:21:11,467
I know exactly what
I'm going to be doing.

1261
01:21:11,500 --> 01:21:13,369
I'm going to be enjoying you

1262
01:21:13,402 --> 01:21:15,204
For the last few weeks
that you're here

1263
01:21:15,238 --> 01:21:16,906
Before you go off to college

1264
01:21:16,940 --> 01:21:19,142
Because there's nothing
more important to me.

1265
01:21:21,710 --> 01:21:25,448
The rest will all
fall into place.

1266
01:21:35,624 --> 01:21:41,464
[***]

1267
01:21:41,497 --> 01:21:45,668
[Jane] Love her,
love her, love her.

1268
01:21:47,603 --> 01:21:51,240
If she favors you,

1269
01:21:51,274 --> 01:21:54,377
Love her.

1270
01:21:55,444 --> 01:21:57,513
If she wounds you,

1271
01:21:59,448 --> 01:22:01,150
Love her.

1272
01:22:01,184 --> 01:22:03,586
If she tears your heart
to pieces

1273
01:22:03,619 --> 01:22:06,322
And as it gets older
and stronger,

1274
01:22:06,355 --> 01:22:09,192
It will tear deeper.

1275
01:22:09,225 --> 01:22:13,462
Love her, love her.

1276
01:22:13,496 --> 01:22:15,431
Love her.

1277
01:22:18,334 --> 01:22:21,070
Everybody needs
a little help sometimes.

1278
01:22:21,104 --> 01:22:23,039
It's nothing to be ashamed of.

1279
01:22:25,174 --> 01:22:27,410
You have a bright future
ahead of you.

1280
01:22:27,443 --> 01:22:29,078
Trust me.

1281
01:22:30,046 --> 01:22:33,082
Your light is very bright,
my dear.

1282
01:22:35,718 --> 01:22:40,256
[***]

